---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { getLangFromUrl } from "../../../i18n/utils";

const lang = getLangFromUrl(Astro.url);
---

<Layout title="Heavy Metal Exposure" lang={lang}>
  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section
    class="max-w-[1200px] w-full mx-auto px-4 py-[50px] md:py-[100px] pt-[150px]"
  >
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2
        class="font-heading font-bold text-[30px] text-brand-primary uppercase tracking-[0.9px] mb-6"
      >
        Heavy Metal Poisoning
      </h2>
      <div
        class="font-body text-brand-text text-[17px] leading-[37px] space-y-4"
      >
        <p>
          Heavy metals are inorganic compounds that the body is not capable of
          metabolizing. Unfortunately, the increase in pollution of all kinds,
          in all types of environments, toxic waste, etc. means that humans are
          exposed to the ingestion, absorption, and exposure of these metals
          which become toxins that the body cannot eliminate. They accumulate in
          organs and tissues, and if not with the help of "chelators"
          (substances that trap the inorganic molecules of heavy metals and
          create compounds that the body *can* eliminate through urine), they
          could not be removed.
        </p>
        <p>
          There are different substances that "chelate" heavy metals. Despite
          this, the presence of heavy metals in tissues creates an
          electromagnetic impregnation. Even if physical elimination is
          successful, this impregnation remains, causing the same symptoms as if
          the heavy metals were still present, seemingly eliminated.
        </p>
        <p>
          Only through the elimination of these frequencies via Bio-resonance
          Mora is complete elimination possible, as well as the restoration of
          the function of the affected tissue.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2
        class="font-heading font-bold text-[30px] text-brand-primary uppercase tracking-[0.9px] mb-6"
      >
        List of Most Common Heavy Metals and Where They Are Found
      </h2>
      <div
        class="font-body text-brand-text text-[17px] leading-[37px] space-y-4"
      >
        <p>
          <strong><span class="underline">ALUMINUM</span></strong>:<br />
          – Accumulates in lungs and brain. Blocks magnesium absorption, causes fatigue,
          and contributes to the onset of Alzheimer's.<br />
          – Found in non-organic vegetables, industrial food, tap water, deodorants,
          amalgams, vaccines, pain relievers, and antacids.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong><span class="underline">ARSENIC</span></strong><br />
          – Accumulates in liver, kidneys, skin, and nervous system.<br />
          – Inhibits the action of vitamin E, selenium, and sulfur. Causes chronic
          fatigue, lung and bladder cancer, diabetes, and gastrointestinal problems.
          found in tap water, packaged juices, whole grains (especially rice), and
          wines.<br />
          To remove arsenic from rice, rinse it several times and boil it in plenty
          of water (about 6 times its volume).
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong><span class="underline">CADMIUM</span></strong><br />
          – Accumulates in the respiratory tract, liver, kidneys, fat, nerves, and
          bones.<br />
          – Blocks the absorption of zinc, magnesium, selenium, and sulfur.<br
          />
          – Causes hypertension, headache, anemia, peripheral nervous system disorders,
          kidney and lung problems.<br />
          – Found in tap water, freshwater fish, crustaceans, leafy vegetables, mushrooms,
          and non-organic dried seaweed.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong><span class="underline">MERCURY</span></strong><br />
          – Accumulates in kidneys, brain, and nervous system.<br />
          – Prevents the absorption of zinc, selenium, and iron. Destroys vitamin
          B12 and causes chronic fatigue, high blood pressure, infections, anemia,
          and immune problems.<br />
          – Found in large fish, intensive agriculture pesticides, vaccines, and dental
          amalgams.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong><span class="underline">LEAD</span></strong><br />
          – Accumulates in the brain, nervous system, and bones. Blocks iron, calcium,
          and molybdenum absorption. Causes musculoskeletal pain, irritability, sleep
          disorders, and cognitive changes.<br />
          – Found in water channeled in lead pipes, pesticides, packaged products,
          medications, tobacco smoke.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong><span class="underline">ALGAE AND MUSHROOMS</span></strong>:
          BEWARE! If they come from contaminated places, they constitute
          authentic heavy metal bombs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 text-center border-t border-gray-200 pt-8">
        <p
          class="font-body text-[17px] leading-[37px] text-blue-600 font-bold mb-4"
        >
          The erasure of metal frequencies via bio-resonance M. guarantees their
          complete elimination.
        </p>
        <p class="font-body text-[17px] leading-[37px] text-brand-text">
          <a
            href="/en/detoxification/"
            class="hover:text-brand-accent transition-colors underline"
            >See the procedure here.</a
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
